cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with linguistic typology and language modelling.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a generative model of language based on matrix factorisation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to model linguistic typology.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the proposed model.
- cs.SD (Sound) is the least likely category as the paper does not seem to involve any discussions on sound or speech processing.
